&lt;li&gt;Serve as first-response for instrument alarms, failures, and performance anomalies during shift, executing in-scope repairs and escalating engineering-level issues to HCE/Automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document all incidents, repairs, and out-of-tolerance conditions in CMMS, and initiate CAPA where required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate day-to-day scheduling and on-site visits with service vendors, track service records, and maintain spare parts inventory for high-priority instruments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to MTBF and downtime tracking, surfacing recurring failure patterns and improvement opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop and refine ME SOPs, work instructions, and the broader ME function as a founding team member&lt;/li&gt;
